hile the pot is brewing. The coffee flow stops while you get your single cup, then resumes automatically when you put the carafe back on the heating pad.","The manufacturer recommends using cone-shaped paper filters for brewing coffee in this automatic drip coffee maker. The cone shape compresses the hot water and coffee grounds together, bringing them into contact longer, which can result in superior-tasting coffee. Unlike some of the best drip coffee makers, however, Kalorik does not give you the option to use the mesh filter alone, so you need to keep buying paper filters for it.","This coffee maker provides a transparent water tank so you can see the water levels easily. However, it does not have a water filter to ensure the clean taste of the coffee, which is standard in the best coffee makers. It also lacks an adjustable heating plate.","If you encounter any difficulties with this coffee maker, you can contact Kalorik through its phone or email support. You get a user manual and a one-year warranty with this device. In its instruction manual, the manufacturer recommends using a commercial cleaning agent to clean and descale this machine instead of the less expensive common white vinegar that is often used for automatic drip coffee makers."]},"id":"3b350608-03c1-4a3d-b7f6-7f6a50ecacd9","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"a600e8e8-9681-4bdd-8c75-b01a9f38dd18","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Kalorik 12-Cup Programmable CM25282R Coffee Maker provides enough features so you can make great coffee. However, you do not get every control and command that a manufacturer could put on a coffee maker with this device. Features such as filter options and an adjustable heating plate hold it back from the convenience of the best coffee machines."]},"id":"fdae08aa-5a83-47e8-9981-06aebb5ea48f","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_57948","url":"/kalorik-12-cup-programmable-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"linda-thomson","ur